    <taskbody>
        <steps>
            <step>
                <cmd>Place your cursor within the text in the tag that you would like to
                        delete.<image placement="break"
                        href="http://beta.cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3A04cae082-7de0-4840-a045-444c0416e53c/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_edm_nln_jp" align="center" scale="80" scalefit="yes"/></cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Right-click on the tag that contains your cursor and select the option
                        <cmdname>Edit Tag</cmdname>.<image placement="break"
                        href="http://beta.cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3Ad63c3930-1011-438d-a7aa-cec27ebaf204/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_xf5_x3v_tp" align="center"/></cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>A pop-up will appear that allows you to add contextual information to
                    tags.</cmd>
                <info>The difference in the list of attributes available in the pop-up will depend
                    on the tag that you are editing.<image placement="break"
                        href="http://beta.cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3Af937a160-f7be-4d06-ada9-f59eae6b1560/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_lwb_bjv_tp" align="center"/></info>
            </step>
        </steps>
        <result>
            <p>Click <cmdname>OK</cmdname> and all edits made to the tag will be saved.</p>
